ar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/87341301?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT","html_url":"https://github.com/GaryDT","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-07-06T07:54:35Z","updated_at":"2022-07-06T15:31:03Z","body":"I'm still getting a null pointer for \"glfwGetJoystickUserPointer\" when either connecting or disconnecting my joystick.\r\n\r\nI'm using Visual Studio 2022 Community Edition and the GLFW 3.3.7 (glfw3.lib) pre-built binary. Incidentally, I'm getting no errors when using \"glfwSetWindowUserPointer\" and \"glfwGetWindowUserPointer\".\r\n\r\nWithin main() I have...\r\n\r\n```\r\nTest test(player);\r\nglfwSetJoystickUserPointer(GLFW_JOYSTICK_1, &test);\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy test class is...\r\n\r\n```\r\nclass Test\r\n{\r\npublic:\r\n\tPlayer& player;\r\n\r\n\tTest(Player& player) : player(player)\r\n\t{\r\n\t\tglfwSetJoystickCallback(joystick_callback);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tstatic void joystick_callback(int joy_id, int joy_event)\r\n\t{\r\n\t\tTest* state = static_cast<Test*>(glfwGetJoystickUserPointer(joy_id));\r\n\t\tstate->player.joystick_connection_event(joy_id, joy_event);\r\n\t}\r\n};\r\n```\r\nPlease confirm if the bug fix should have fixed my null pointer issue?\r\n\r\nCheers, Gary.\r\n\r\n**Edit:** I'm just doing the below (locally within the relevant Player class function) as a workaround for now, which seems sufficient compared to controlling the situation from the joystick callback. \r\n\r\n```\r\naxes = glfwGetJoystickAxes(GLFW_JOYSTICK_1, &num_axes);\r\nif (axes != NULL)\r\n\tjoystick_connected = true;\r\nelse\r\n\tjoystick_connected = false;\r\n```","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/comments/1175904228/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"GaryDT","id":87341301,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg3MzQxMzAx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/87341301?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT","html_url":"https://github.com/GaryDT","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GaryDT/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/comments/1176528571","html_url":"https://github.com/glfw/glfw/issues/2092#issuecomment-1176528571","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/2092","id":1176528571,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAJFXBc5GIGa7","user":{"login":"elmindreda","id":133714,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzMzcxNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/133714?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda","html_url":"https://github.com/elmindreda","